00:26:24.253 --> 00:26:26.242
And the Delta Dirt Distillery.

00:26:27.516 --> 00:26:28.875
Oh, we're closed.

00:26:30.163 --> 00:26:32.542
Buy appointment open but that looks cool.

00:26:33.790 --> 00:26:36.047
Got all these cameras up here.
Check that out.

00:26:36.114 --> 00:26:39.290
All the cameras in the light post.
First National Bank.

00:26:40.330 --> 00:26:43.399
It's one of these
yellow line walking tours.

00:26:43.466 --> 00:26:45.962
As in, can walk down
the middle of the road.

00:26:46.396 --> 00:26:48.278
And you're in the way of nobody.

00:26:50.140 --> 00:26:52.493
Wonder what this old grand building was.

00:26:53.033 --> 00:26:55.299
Its massive columns. Maybe a hotel.

00:26:58.242 --> 00:27:00.920
Just holes in the sides of buildings here.

00:27:04.930 --> 00:27:06.753
You can see that old floor.

00:27:06.820 --> 00:27:09.004
Maybe a pharmacy, general store.

00:27:11.800 --> 00:27:15.751
So within recent years,
this place is known for crime.

00:27:15.818 --> 00:27:18.533
95 homicides per 100,000.

00:27:18.600 --> 00:27:24.136
Which puts it way above Little Rock,
Memphis, even St. Louis.

00:27:24.556 --> 00:27:28.934
Now it's a much smaller town,
so we're talking per capita, obviously.

00:27:29.001 --> 00:27:32.515
The US average is 5 per 100,000.

00:27:32.980 --> 00:27:36.311
19 times the US average.

00:27:38.031 --> 00:27:40.560
Looks to be one of the few businesses open.

00:27:48.365 --> 00:27:51.259
-[woman] Hello, how you doing?
-Doing well. How are you doing?

00:27:51.326 --> 00:27:52.103
Alright.

00:27:52.170 --> 00:27:54.431
-Is this your business?
-Yes, sir.

00:27:54.491 --> 00:27:56.280
-How's it going?
-It's going great.

00:27:56.347 --> 00:27:59.178
I'm doing great. I'm making a Delta video.

00:27:59.620 --> 00:28:02.478
-And I like to show small businesses.
-Okay, awesome.

00:28:02.545 --> 00:28:03.949
-Represent.
-No problem.

00:28:04.016 --> 00:28:05.721
So, how's it going?

00:28:05.788 --> 00:28:08.186
-Everything's going great.
-That's cool.

00:28:08.259 --> 00:28:11.671
Really, it's our thrift thing.
Muphet and Mysta Marketplace.

00:28:11.752 --> 00:28:13.735
We've been in business now for a year.

00:28:13.802 --> 00:28:15.478
I really appreciate the community

00:28:15.545 --> 00:28:18.860
because they have been great
with the donations and supporting.

00:28:18.927 --> 00:28:20.868
As you can see, they're shopping.

00:28:21.296 --> 00:28:23.233
-Can you walk us around?
-Sure.

00:28:23.863 --> 00:28:27.997
The idea of our business
was to give back to the community,

00:28:28.064 --> 00:28:30.351
to make them feel good about shopping.

00:28:30.418 --> 00:28:32.335
-Coming downtown to shop?
-Yeah.

00:28:32.402 --> 00:28:35.177
Like bring some life down here
outside of gonna the bank

00:28:35.244 --> 00:28:38.472
and gonna KIPP school, of course,
and getting some good barbecue.

00:28:38.539 --> 00:28:42.786
I want them to feel, hey, I may not
can get it at the expensive store,

00:28:42.853 --> 00:28:45.405
but I know
Muphet and Mysta Marketplace got it.

00:28:45.472 --> 00:28:48.317
-And they're gonna give me a great deal.
-You have great deals?

00:28:48.384 --> 00:28:49.659
-Yes.
-I mean, five bucks.

00:28:49.726 --> 00:28:51.249
-Yes.
-You're not beating that.

00:28:51.316 --> 00:28:54.566
The most expensive thing in my marketplace
would be my furniture.

00:28:54.633 --> 00:28:58.123
You're not even out of 500 bucks,
you can get a whole living room set.

00:28:58.190 --> 00:28:59.073
Okay, cool.

00:28:59.140 --> 00:29:01.490
-I can remember
when I was a little girl and…

00:29:01.557 --> 00:29:05.148
I would be excited to come down here
on Saturdays with my mom.

00:29:05.562 --> 00:29:08.007
And we would start from
this end of Cherry,

00:29:08.074 --> 00:29:10.457
where this statue is
down beside Miss Anne's.

00:29:10.538 --> 00:29:12.965
-All the way at the end?
-All the way at the end.

00:29:13.032 --> 00:29:16.462
And it would be just cars
before it was shut down.

00:29:16.529 --> 00:29:18.519
-So we're talking late 80s?
-Yes.

00:29:18.896 --> 00:29:20.836
That's wild. Okay, so what happened?

00:29:20.903 --> 00:29:23.777
Well, I guess everybody started…
the older ones start,

00:29:23.850 --> 00:29:26.919
you know, passing away
and the young ones started getting it.

00:29:26.986 --> 00:29:31.877
And, you know, nobody really just had
the love and passion for it anymore.

00:29:31.944 --> 00:29:35.573
I guess with us being always in
the light of being in the crime

00:29:35.640 --> 00:29:39.723
and Helena is bad, you know, it's kind of
like a stigma that's on the city.

00:29:39.790 --> 00:29:43.155
But really, I've been here my whole life
and Helena is not that bad.

00:29:43.222 --> 00:29:44.213
It's affordable.

00:29:44.280 --> 00:29:46.330
Everything is going up everywhere you go.

00:29:46.397 --> 00:29:50.397
People are quick to say it's nothing here,
there are no jobs. I'm gonna leave.

00:29:50.464 --> 00:29:54.656
Well, what I decided to do was
create a space where people can actually

00:29:54.723 --> 00:29:56.467
look forward to something.

00:29:56.534 --> 00:29:57.996
It's a small business.

00:29:58.063 --> 00:30:01.890
But hey, we are creating a place
where you need something to do.

00:30:01.957 --> 00:30:03.073
You can come in.

00:30:03.669 --> 00:30:06.269
Volunteer work.
You know, I coordinate with the school.

00:30:06.336 --> 00:30:10.013
If the kids come in and they want to do
some hours or something like that.

00:30:10.080 --> 00:30:12.669
So it just starts small.
It may not be big.

00:30:12.743 --> 00:30:15.880
Then my husband and I,
we brought the U-Haul business here.

00:30:15.947 --> 00:30:16.830
-Oh, cool.

00:30:16.897 --> 00:30:19.513
It was here before
but it wasn't on this side of town.

00:30:19.580 --> 00:30:21.356
That has been a great success.

00:30:21.423 --> 00:30:23.658
The community
has been very supportive.

00:30:23.725 --> 00:30:24.608
That's great.

00:30:24.675 --> 00:30:26.834
They've been supporting, showing that love.

00:30:26.901 --> 00:30:28.866
I'm just glad that I can give it back.

00:30:28.933 --> 00:30:30.810
-You got a great attitude.
-Thank you.

00:30:30.877 --> 00:30:33.377
-I try to always stay positive.
-That's everything.

00:30:33.444 --> 00:30:35.194
No matter what. Hey, it's not easy.

00:30:35.261 --> 00:30:39.479
It's not easy at all, but you have to have
a positive mindset

00:30:39.546 --> 00:30:42.496
to do something like this,
especially being an entrepreneur.

00:30:42.563 --> 00:30:44.700
-Yeah. But you're making it.
-Exactly.

00:30:44.767 --> 00:30:47.468
-You're getting by, paying your bills.
-Exactly.

00:30:47.535 --> 00:30:48.809
-Awesome.
-You know what I'm saying?

00:30:48.876 --> 00:30:52.426
You don't just come out ballin' and rich.
It's about what you put in it.

00:30:52.493 --> 00:30:55.815
And I've learned that what you put in it
is what you get out of it.

00:30:55.882 --> 00:30:58.536
So, if you just go there and just do some…
you're gonna get some…

00:30:58.603 --> 00:31:01.399
But if you go there
and you put intent behind it,

00:31:01.466 --> 00:31:03.766
what you're expecting,
and you get to see that.

00:31:03.833 --> 00:31:06.763
My intention was when people
come in here and shop with me,

00:31:06.830 --> 00:31:10.074
they're walking out smiling
because they they got the best deals.

00:31:10.141 --> 00:31:12.676
Yeah, I gotta say,
I'm all over the country.

00:31:12.744 --> 00:31:15.270
-Wow.
-And I love architecture.

00:31:15.816 --> 00:31:19.855
You guys have great architecture,
like it has such potential.

00:31:19.922 --> 00:31:21.136
-Yes, it does.
-Right?

00:31:21.203 --> 00:31:25.226
It takes people like you,
that, you know, are courageous,

00:31:25.293 --> 00:31:27.273
and you sort of go for it, right?

00:31:27.340 --> 00:31:29.943
And you plant a stake and
then other people are like,

00:31:30.010 --> 00:31:33.206
"Maybe I can maybe do something
over there in that building."

00:31:33.273 --> 00:31:34.407
And then it catches.

00:31:34.474 --> 00:31:37.052
So if it went down that quickly,

00:31:37.717 --> 00:31:38.976
there's the possibility.

00:31:39.539 --> 00:31:40.931
Places are always doing like this.

00:31:40.998 --> 00:31:42.498
-They're always cycling.
-Yes.

00:31:42.565 --> 00:31:45.185
And so maybe it's at the bottom
coming up a little.

00:31:45.252 --> 00:31:47.580
-Right.
-I don't know, it's my first time here.

00:31:47.647 --> 00:31:48.721
It just takes time.

00:31:48.788 --> 00:31:53.146
I don't want your first impression to be
oh God, it's crime, nothing there to do.

00:31:53.213 --> 00:31:54.266
It has its

00:31:55.340 --> 00:31:56.702
great features about it.

00:31:56.769 --> 00:31:58.061
-Good people?
-Yes.

00:31:58.128 --> 00:31:59.650
It's home, it's down South.

00:31:59.717 --> 00:32:01.694
People I know, when I was a little girl.

00:32:01.761 --> 00:32:03.918
You have some that's still around,
you know?

00:32:03.985 --> 00:32:06.168
So it's just the wise, it's the charm here.

00:32:06.235 --> 00:32:07.935
That's what makes me hang around.

00:32:08.002 --> 00:32:09.293
-I like Arkansas.
-Yeah.

00:32:10.310 --> 00:32:14.074
All right, guys, if you're coming through
here, you're on a great road trip.

00:32:14.141 --> 00:32:16.407
You know, a lot of Europeans
see these videos.

00:32:16.474 --> 00:32:20.780
I only know because I got the comments
from Germans, from Dutch people,

00:32:20.860 --> 00:32:23.892
people from all over saying
"I went to some of those places."

00:32:23.959 --> 00:32:25.818
and a lot of Americans too of course.

00:32:25.885 --> 00:32:27.331
"And I had a great time."

00:32:27.405 --> 00:32:30.363
So businesses like this could really

00:32:31.103 --> 00:32:32.231
use your help.

00:32:32.298 --> 00:32:34.973
Just coming in and buying something

00:32:35.770 --> 00:32:37.216
or saying hi.

00:32:37.968 --> 00:32:39.928
You know, people tend to like that.

00:32:39.995 --> 00:32:43.962
Cause look, she's doing
a pretty hard thing here, I would think.

00:32:44.816 --> 00:32:47.348
And I respect someone that does that.

00:32:47.843 --> 00:32:49.643
In a place like this it's not easy.

00:32:50.136 --> 00:32:51.312
Look at this beauty.

00:32:51.956 --> 00:32:53.069
Oh wow.

00:32:53.136 --> 00:32:54.554
"Sensational lounge."

00:32:57.574 --> 00:33:01.129
Oh, look at those old tables and the bar.

00:33:03.046 --> 00:33:05.573
Delta Que and Brew, Taste the hype.

00:33:06.816 --> 00:33:07.992
Look at this set up.

00:33:10.742 --> 00:33:13.683
Right, we're not getting in though.
It is a Monday.

00:33:15.656 --> 00:33:19.480
I'm sure there's some good street activity
here when they're open.

00:33:21.301 --> 00:33:22.830
Got some hoops over there.

00:33:23.298 --> 00:33:27.244
And guys, I really make an effort
not to show kids up close

00:33:27.311 --> 00:33:29.943
without their parents saying it's cool.

00:33:30.010 --> 00:33:33.407
But you can see kids hanging out,
little hoops going on here.

00:33:33.873 --> 00:33:35.506
We got the Red Ball Store.

00:33:36.129 --> 00:33:39.564
Music, Delta Blues, big thing here.

00:33:39.631 --> 00:33:41.632
But you can see
they're trying to bring people in.

00:33:41.699 --> 00:33:43.688
They got this stage over here.

00:33:45.363 --> 00:33:50.056
That's never a good sign when you see
the gang tags up on stop signs.

00:33:52.469 --> 00:33:54.776
Then it just sort of dies off here.

00:33:54.843 --> 00:33:56.715
Once you get off the main street.

00:33:56.782 --> 00:33:59.311
And look,
the population's declined so much.

00:33:59.772 --> 00:34:01.287
These buildings, people leave,

00:34:01.354 --> 00:34:04.286
and then the demo unit
doesn't come in to take it all down.

00:34:04.353 --> 00:34:07.284
They're just left
and that's why they start deteriorating.

00:34:07.351 --> 00:34:10.013
Nature comes back, starts taking them over.

00:34:11.049 --> 00:34:13.323
But all sorts of blues history here.

00:34:14.129 --> 00:34:15.503
"Putting blues on the air.

00:34:15.570 --> 00:34:16.923
It's King Biscuit time.

00:34:17.878 --> 00:34:19.239
Pass the biscuits!

00:34:19.716 --> 00:34:22.381
Sunshine Sunny Payne."

00:34:30.966 --> 00:34:32.713
Got a water situation here.

00:34:33.506 --> 00:34:34.918
Looks like a pipe burst.

00:34:36.470 --> 00:34:38.120
Got an old motel here.

00:34:38.916 --> 00:34:40.646
Cool old school 50s sign.

00:34:41.126 --> 00:34:45.013
And people would come from all over
for the blues back in the day

00:34:45.080 --> 00:34:46.727
when this place was thriving.

00:34:47.129 --> 00:34:48.541
The economy was pumping.

00:34:49.559 --> 00:34:51.232
Music filling the streets.

00:34:53.040 --> 00:34:55.301
-Sir, how you doing?
-Hey, how you doing, man?

00:34:55.368 --> 00:34:57.558
-Good. I'm trying to meet some locals.
-Okay.

00:34:57.625 --> 00:34:59.163
I'm one of a locals.

00:34:59.230 --> 00:35:01.699
-This is your funeral home?
How things going?

00:35:02.130 --> 00:35:03.303
It's the Delta.

00:35:03.370 --> 00:35:06.152
You're dealing with
the poorest county in the Arkansas.

00:35:06.219 --> 00:35:07.997
The Delta is like,

00:35:08.064 --> 00:35:10.677
to the people in Little Rock, Fayetteville,

00:35:10.744 --> 00:35:11.810
and all of them,

00:35:11.883 --> 00:35:15.711
it's like the forgotten area of the state.

00:35:16.099 --> 00:35:18.936
-You guys feel forgotten out here?
-Yeah, we do.

00:35:19.003 --> 00:35:21.769
A lot of the resources,
it's not coming this way.

00:35:21.836 --> 00:35:24.076
You're dealing with 70% Black,

00:35:24.467 --> 00:35:28.172
30% White, and then just the area.

00:35:28.239 --> 00:35:30.536
So what they do,
they pull the resources away,

00:35:30.970 --> 00:35:33.057
and they don't really come down.

00:35:33.509 --> 00:35:36.649
The governor or none of that
comes down really in this area.

00:35:36.716 --> 00:35:40.812
So anytime that you have poverty,
you're gonna have crime.

00:35:41.252 --> 00:35:45.498
Probably the second most dangerous city
in the state of Arkansas.

00:35:45.565 --> 00:35:47.680
-Pine Bluff, number one?
-Yeah, Pine Bluff.

00:35:47.747 --> 00:35:48.926
-I was there.
-Yeah.

00:35:48.993 --> 00:35:50.907
So it's the same thing, right?

00:35:50.974 --> 00:35:53.282
-Nice people, though.
I mean, I was in and out.

00:35:53.349 --> 00:35:57.188
I'm not living there, so I don't really
know. But I met a lot of nice people.

00:35:57.255 --> 00:35:59.253
A lot of nice people here.

00:35:59.320 --> 00:36:03.146
When I lived here, I didn't live here.
I lived in a little town called Alexa.

00:36:03.213 --> 00:36:06.055
-It's in the country.
-I cruised through. That's nice.

00:36:06.122 --> 00:36:09.093
Yeah, small town.
Now that's where everybody's migrating to.

00:36:09.160 --> 00:36:12.216
There was a time when
they didn't want to come to the country.

00:36:12.283 --> 00:36:16.103
And now everybody wants to because
you don't have that crime and people,

00:36:16.170 --> 00:36:17.713
They're getting away from the city.

00:36:17.780 --> 00:36:21.983
We had a lot of industries here
back in the day.

00:36:22.050 --> 00:36:26.080
When you start getting into
lawsuits and people falling,

00:36:26.147 --> 00:36:29.780
and everybody's trying to
get up on something, you know.

00:36:29.847 --> 00:36:31.810
And the people, they just start leaving

00:36:31.877 --> 00:36:33.877
because they didn't want their children,

00:36:33.944 --> 00:36:36.613
after they finished school,
they have no job for them.

00:36:36.680 --> 00:36:38.205
The parents had retired.

00:36:38.272 --> 00:36:41.963
So what they did,
a lot of them sold their homes

00:36:42.520 --> 00:36:45.025
and moved up in the hills

00:36:45.092 --> 00:36:47.319
or moved out from West Helena.

00:36:47.386 --> 00:36:50.436
-So who's committing most of the crime?
It's young men, right?

00:36:50.503 --> 00:36:52.686
Right. Just a lot of break-ins.

00:36:52.753 --> 00:36:55.420
Is it like 12-year-olds
to like 30-year-olds?

00:36:55.487 --> 00:36:56.533
Teenagers.

00:36:56.600 --> 00:37:00.193
A lot of gunfire
and it's just like Iraq at night.

00:37:00.260 --> 00:37:02.710
-Do you hear it?
-Oh yeah, I hear it all the time.

00:37:02.777 --> 00:37:06.882
It's all over the city
but it's usually over the levee area.

00:37:06.954 --> 00:37:10.083
-Over the levee?
-Yeah, there's a levee right here.

00:37:10.150 --> 00:37:12.292
You can see
the little crest part right there.

00:37:12.793 --> 00:37:14.010
That's called the levee.

00:37:14.077 --> 00:37:17.523
-So the one big employer in town,
chemical manufacturing, right?

00:37:17.590 --> 00:37:19.387
-On the outskirts?
-Yeah.

00:37:19.454 --> 00:37:23.672
And of course the Dough Boy
that makes the swimming pools.

00:37:23.739 --> 00:37:26.206
-You can get a good job here.
-Yeah, yeah.

00:37:26.273 --> 00:37:30.483
But the problem is
being able to pass a drug test.

00:37:31.083 --> 00:37:33.894
And things like that,
see, that's sticky, you know?

00:37:34.566 --> 00:37:37.586
-A lot of people can't pass it, huh?
-Can't pass a drug test.

00:37:37.653 --> 00:37:38.628
Is weed in on that?

00:37:38.695 --> 00:37:42.869
Weed, people all the time,
"We need to bring some jobs here."

00:37:42.936 --> 00:37:45.036
Well, who the hell's gonna work them?

00:37:45.103 --> 00:37:47.575
If you bring the jobs here,
who's gonna work them?

00:37:47.642 --> 00:37:50.713
If you have some people
that's not learned enough, can't read,

00:37:50.780 --> 00:37:55.303
that understand, because anytime that
you have poverty, you're gonna have crime.

00:37:55.370 --> 00:37:56.588
I have a good life here.

00:37:56.655 --> 00:37:58.791
I've been here 26 years.

00:37:58.858 --> 00:38:00.081
I moved from New Jersey.

00:38:00.148 --> 00:38:02.956
I was born and reared here,
but I came back and opened a business.

00:38:03.023 --> 00:38:04.585
I've been in business 26 years.

00:38:04.652 --> 00:38:07.700
We have a great living here,
because I mind my business.

00:38:07.767 --> 00:38:10.037
I do what I have to do.

00:38:10.104 --> 00:38:12.291
I don't get involved in anything else.

00:38:12.696 --> 00:38:14.016
-Well, I appreciate you.

00:38:14.083 --> 00:38:18.099
I'm making a video on the Delta,
and this is how we learn from the locals.

00:38:18.166 --> 00:38:21.048
The ones that'll just
tell you the truth about it.

00:38:29.578 --> 00:38:30.716
I'm Ced, man.

00:38:30.783 --> 00:38:32.438
-Sid?
-Yeah, C-E-D.

00:38:32.903 --> 00:38:33.786
Peter.

00:38:33.853 --> 00:38:34.736
-Peter?
-Yeah.

00:38:34.803 --> 00:38:36.027
Okay, I'm Ced.

00:38:36.094 --> 00:38:37.278
You grew up here, Ced?

00:38:37.345 --> 00:38:40.413
-Born and raised right here in Helena.
-All right, how is it?

00:38:40.480 --> 00:38:42.002
-You like it?
-I love it.

00:38:42.069 --> 00:38:44.775
-You love it?
-I love it. I love this city, man.

00:38:44.842 --> 00:38:47.747
I get a peace of mind here.

00:38:47.814 --> 00:38:49.394
I don't know about nobody else.

00:38:49.461 --> 00:38:51.509
I got self-control over me.

00:38:52.100 --> 00:38:53.464
I run my destiny.

00:38:53.531 --> 00:38:54.943
What I want to do, I do.

