00:52:25.686 --> 00:52:26.569
[woman giggles]

00:52:27.140 --> 00:52:28.462
Oh, your monitoring.

00:52:28.529 --> 00:52:30.764
-How's crime?
Is there much crime or no?

00:52:31.179 --> 00:52:32.782
-No. Not really.

00:52:32.849 --> 00:52:34.264
 Not a whole lot of crime.

00:52:34.331 --> 00:52:36.566
But they set my laundry mat on fire.

00:52:36.983 --> 00:52:39.017
-They set it on fire?
-Mm-hmm.

00:52:39.084 --> 00:52:42.044
-When did that happen?
-July the 10th.

00:52:42.513 --> 00:52:43.396
-Oh.
-Last year.

00:52:45.400 --> 00:52:47.867
[woman] Small, suppressed town.

00:52:48.886 --> 00:52:51.136
[Peter] But you're
making something out of it?

00:52:51.203 --> 00:52:52.879
-Yeah.
-You're making a go?

00:52:52.946 --> 00:52:54.354
I'm trying. It's hard.

00:52:54.953 --> 00:52:56.113
And I work.

00:52:56.180 --> 00:52:58.931
Friday, Saturday, and Sunday,
at Lennox in Stuttgart.

00:52:59.546 --> 00:53:01.059
Building air conditioning.

00:53:01.126 --> 00:53:02.951
-I believe your belt's worn out.
-Oh.

00:53:03.018 --> 00:53:05.194
It's spinning, but it ain't catching.

00:53:05.750 --> 00:53:07.057
-You're from here?
-Yeah.

00:53:07.579 --> 00:53:09.381
Okay, what was it like growing up?

00:53:09.806 --> 00:53:12.054
It was a lot more.

00:53:12.121 --> 00:53:13.515
Everybody moved away.

00:53:14.020 --> 00:53:15.432
Why didn't you take off?

00:53:15.826 --> 00:53:18.591
I was the one that stayed
and took care of mama.

00:53:19.066 --> 00:53:20.026
Yup.

00:53:20.093 --> 00:53:22.953
Now I'm ready to go
'cause my kids done got grown.

00:53:23.020 --> 00:53:25.552
-They grown?
The school shut down here though, huh?

00:53:25.619 --> 00:53:26.502
Yeah.

00:53:26.569 --> 00:53:29.378
And my daughter graduated
on the 13th from Phillips

00:53:29.864 --> 00:53:31.389
at the RN program.

00:53:31.456 --> 00:53:32.339
-Okay. Congrats.

00:53:32.406 --> 00:53:34.034
So she's moving to Little Rock.

00:53:34.101 --> 00:53:35.520
-Congrats. I was just there.

00:53:35.587 --> 00:53:37.779
Mm-hmm.
She's gonna be working at Baptist.

00:53:37.846 --> 00:53:39.552
She's got a job offer there.

00:53:40.179 --> 00:53:42.238
-You pretty happy about that?
-Yeah.

00:53:42.779 --> 00:53:45.661
I used to tell her all the time that

00:53:46.771 --> 00:53:48.034
why leave?

00:53:48.101 --> 00:53:49.859
You know, get your degree and leave.

00:53:49.926 --> 00:53:51.691
You can make something happen here.

00:53:51.758 --> 00:53:54.180
She always wanted
to be a nurse all her life.

00:53:54.247 --> 00:53:55.130
-Okay.

00:53:55.197 --> 00:53:59.266
So I always wanted her to be like,
start a nursing home.

00:53:59.333 --> 00:54:00.216
You a nurse?

00:54:00.646 --> 00:54:02.985
Even if you start with eight people.

00:54:03.436 --> 00:54:08.159
I raised… well, I'm gonna say I raised,
I'm raising my mama now.

00:54:09.032 --> 00:54:11.698
'Cause she got dementia
and she has Alzheimer's.

00:54:11.765 --> 00:54:13.589
So I'm kind of keeping her now.

00:54:14.069 --> 00:54:18.222
And it be times where I just need
a break for about a week or so.

00:54:18.715 --> 00:54:21.619
And that'll be good, you know,
to have a place

00:54:21.686 --> 00:54:24.559
where you can drop them off
and be all right for at least a week.

00:54:24.626 --> 00:54:27.317
Yeah. Is there anything like that out here?

00:54:27.384 --> 00:54:28.455
No. [scoffs]

00:54:29.672 --> 00:54:30.555
No.

00:54:31.000 --> 00:54:33.710
And she wanted to stay
and then it's just like

00:54:34.438 --> 00:54:36.558
a lot of hate, suppression.

00:54:37.589 --> 00:54:40.074
And she afraid if she try to,

00:54:40.141 --> 00:54:41.978
you know, do stuff here,

00:54:42.870 --> 00:54:47.039
people will, you know,
just like report false accusations.

00:54:47.106 --> 00:54:49.827
And sometimes you gotta
prove your innocence.

00:54:49.901 --> 00:54:51.456
You get a lawyer 'cause

00:54:52.069 --> 00:54:54.808
here in Phillips County,
they can really accuse you.

00:54:54.875 --> 00:54:58.377
Fill out an affidavit,
accuse you of something that you didn't do.

00:54:58.444 --> 00:55:00.923
-And then you got to get a lawyer.
-Who does that?

00:55:00.990 --> 00:55:01.972
Your people.

00:55:02.039 --> 00:55:04.392
-Oh, the community, someone in town.
-Yeah.

00:55:04.760 --> 00:55:07.180
They don't like you
'cause they think you better,

00:55:07.254 --> 00:55:10.472
but you're really not better than them,
you just want different.

00:55:10.539 --> 00:55:11.889
So you think different.

00:55:11.956 --> 00:55:14.601
-Okay, so yeah,
if you want to better yourself,

00:55:15.183 --> 00:55:16.734
then some people don't like that.

00:55:16.801 --> 00:55:17.699
Right.

00:55:17.766 --> 00:55:18.679
-Okay.

00:55:18.746 --> 00:55:20.688
It's a little hate, right.

00:55:20.755 --> 00:55:23.196
This town is
really fighting with each other.

00:55:23.263 --> 00:55:24.758
-Really?
-Yeah.

00:55:25.220 --> 00:55:26.925
-As we speak?
-Mm-hmm.

00:55:26.992 --> 00:55:29.120
-Is it like Bloods and Crips stuff or what?

00:55:29.187 --> 00:55:30.564
No. No, it's not.

00:55:30.631 --> 00:55:32.542
It's more of…

00:55:35.820 --> 00:55:37.743
with the Black community, we don't?

00:55:38.677 --> 00:55:40.479
We don't uplift each other.

00:55:40.546 --> 00:55:43.346
We feel like
'cause you want to do something,

00:55:44.364 --> 00:55:47.681
they feel like with the mayor,
she got going on.

00:55:48.119 --> 00:55:53.479
It's a lot of Black people don't like
what she doing because they not doing it.

00:55:53.992 --> 00:55:54.875
-I just met her.

00:55:55.446 --> 00:55:56.329
Yeah.

00:55:56.396 --> 00:55:59.044
-She seems pretty fired up on the town.
-Yeah.

00:55:59.111 --> 00:56:02.996
I'll tell you one thing,
she did more for this little small town

00:56:03.063 --> 00:56:05.122
than anybody I have ever seen done.

00:56:05.683 --> 00:56:07.494
-In all your years?
-In all my years.

00:56:07.561 --> 00:56:10.003
-That's so cool.
-And she got grants.

00:56:11.209 --> 00:56:13.259
The mayor don't get paid nothing here.

00:56:13.326 --> 00:56:15.632
I think $700 or something.

00:56:15.699 --> 00:56:16.582
-A month?

00:56:16.649 --> 00:56:17.792
-A month.
-Ouch.

00:56:17.859 --> 00:56:20.116
Yeah. How can you live off that?

00:56:20.183 --> 00:56:22.390
And she, I know, put in 40 hours.

00:56:22.809 --> 00:56:25.103
I don't agree with everything she does.

00:56:25.533 --> 00:56:26.910
-But…
-That's life, yeah.

00:56:26.977 --> 00:56:28.721
Yeah. I respect her.

00:56:28.788 --> 00:56:30.399
-But she cares about the town?

00:56:30.466 --> 00:56:32.995
-Yeah, I think she cares about it.
-Alright.

00:56:33.062 --> 00:56:35.769
Yeah, 'cause we got a water grant.

00:56:36.413 --> 00:56:38.175
Have you seen our water tower?

00:56:38.242 --> 00:56:40.978
The worst water tower
in the United States.

00:56:42.400 --> 00:56:46.566
Main Street divides,
still divides even to this day.

00:56:48.372 --> 00:56:49.822
Black side, White side.

00:56:50.455 --> 00:56:54.043
It's like two Black people
that stay on this side of the town.

00:56:54.559 --> 00:56:56.759
Black people stay over here,
no White people.

00:56:56.826 --> 00:57:00.232
-So if I cross the Main Street,
it's just gonna be Whites over there?

00:57:00.299 --> 00:57:01.843
Pretty much. Just two people.

00:57:01.910 --> 00:57:03.632
You guys don't get along?

00:57:03.699 --> 00:57:05.787
It's not that they don't get along.

00:57:05.854 --> 00:57:07.619
It's kind of like that secret.

00:57:08.688 --> 00:57:09.772
You know?

00:57:09.839 --> 00:57:13.791
You don't see any White kids and Black kids
playing with each other here.

00:57:13.858 --> 00:57:15.272
Like, you will never see.

00:57:15.339 --> 00:57:17.860
Like, no more than softball.

00:57:17.927 --> 00:57:21.267
They'll come get Black kids
to participate in

00:57:21.698 --> 00:57:24.951
T-ball and softball
because it's not enough here.

00:57:25.018 --> 00:57:29.710
But as far as you seeing White kids
and Black kids riding they bikes together,

00:57:29.777 --> 00:57:30.942
that will never happen.

00:57:31.008 --> 00:57:33.462
-Why is it still like that here
do you think?

00:57:33.529 --> 00:57:37.711
I think it's embedded in people

00:57:37.778 --> 00:57:42.290
and it's just like nobody here
that's really trying to break the cycle.

00:57:42.860 --> 00:57:45.036
I actually bought a house over there.

00:57:45.966 --> 00:57:47.667
-You live over there?
-Yeah.

00:57:47.734 --> 00:57:50.902
-They're cool with you living over there?
-Not really.

00:57:50.969 --> 00:57:52.498
Why'd you move over there?

00:57:53.006 --> 00:57:55.935
Um, I think because, one,

00:57:56.468 --> 00:57:58.729
that's where the house was for sale at.

00:57:58.796 --> 00:58:01.032
And I'm determined.

00:58:01.099 --> 00:58:03.260
If I can't, I can show you I can.

00:58:03.327 --> 00:58:06.246
You know, you tell me I can't
have this or I can't do that,

00:58:06.313 --> 00:58:09.931
-…that's my motivation, to do it.
-That's why I like you.

00:58:09.998 --> 00:58:11.617
-I'm the same way.
-Yeah.

00:58:12.490 --> 00:58:14.438
It's a big, big thing here,

00:58:14.852 --> 00:58:15.735
racism.

00:58:16.683 --> 00:58:18.305
But you get along with him.

00:58:18.372 --> 00:58:20.982
Yeah, I get along
with a lot of White people.

00:58:21.049 --> 00:58:23.060
-But he's cool with you?
-Yeah.

00:58:23.127 --> 00:58:25.582
-Okay, so it's not everyone, obviously.

00:58:25.649 --> 00:58:27.825
He's not from here. He's from DeWitt.

00:58:28.733 --> 00:58:29.725
Where's that?

00:58:29.792 --> 00:58:32.605
It's about 45 miles from here.

00:58:33.016 --> 00:58:35.910
-So it's totally different there?
-Totally different.

00:58:35.977 --> 00:58:39.448
-Okay, so it really depends
the town you're in in the Delta,

00:58:40.306 --> 00:58:42.050
where those dynamics take play?

00:58:42.117 --> 00:58:43.123
Right.

00:58:43.190 --> 00:58:47.153
The lady, she was telling me
that she was gonna sell the house.

00:58:47.220 --> 00:58:50.173
And every time she get ready
to sell it to somebody Black,

00:58:50.240 --> 00:58:52.361
somebody White'll try to get it.

00:58:52.428 --> 00:58:56.199
They'll be like, "I'm gonna get it."
and finally she sold it to me.

00:58:56.266 --> 00:58:58.516
So that's how
I got my first house over there.

00:58:58.583 --> 00:59:01.627
-If you don't mind me asking,
how much did you buy it for?

00:59:01.694 --> 00:59:04.146
-$40,000.
-40 grand?! Wow.

00:59:04.786 --> 00:59:07.455
So a house in this town,
you can get for 40 grand?

00:59:07.522 --> 00:59:08.405
Yeah.

00:59:08.799 --> 00:59:11.288
 -Even cheaper, right?
-Well, you could. Yeah.

00:59:11.355 --> 00:59:13.213
But there's no houses here.

00:59:13.280 --> 00:59:14.463
Nothing for sale?

00:59:14.530 --> 00:59:18.530
Nothing for sale 'cause nobody's
putting nothing back into this town.

00:59:19.026 --> 00:59:21.509
-So it's just deteriorating.
-But it's up to you guys.

00:59:21.576 --> 00:59:22.710
-Yeah, it's up to us.

00:59:22.777 --> 00:59:25.134
-No one from the outside
is gonna save the day.

00:59:25.201 --> 00:59:28.129
No. That's why I put in three tiny houses.

00:59:28.818 --> 00:59:31.442
He came in and wired my third tiny house.

00:59:32.006 --> 00:59:32.988
-Okay.

00:59:33.055 --> 00:59:34.639
And I already had two.

00:59:34.706 --> 00:59:38.127
They on Allen Street,
the street behind the Dollar General.

00:59:38.666 --> 00:59:40.559
-I'll check them out.
-Check them out.

00:59:40.626 --> 00:59:42.676
-They're new ones.
-Yeah. They like sheds.

00:59:42.743 --> 00:59:45.600
And I turned them into Airbnbs.

00:59:46.213 --> 00:59:47.476
-Airbnbs?

00:59:47.543 --> 00:59:50.193
-Yeah. You should stay there.
-People are coming here?

00:59:50.260 --> 00:59:53.621
In the wintertime I attract
a lot of out-of-state hunters.

00:59:53.688 --> 00:59:56.493
-Oh, the hunters come in?
-Yeah. They come in and hunt.

00:59:56.939 --> 00:59:59.233
-So this is how you started it?
-Mm-hmm.

01:00:00.343 --> 01:00:02.441
'Cause property go real cheap here.

01:00:02.508 --> 01:00:06.859
-Blood, sweat, and tears.
First tiny house Airbnb, 85% completed.

01:00:06.926 --> 01:00:09.533
You got all these guys
to help you bring it in.

01:00:09.992 --> 01:00:12.616
-Where do people work here in town?
-Out of town.

01:00:13.113 --> 01:00:14.496
Like, I work in Stuttgart.

01:00:14.563 --> 01:00:16.676
And that's like an hour and 25 minutes.

01:00:16.743 --> 01:00:19.102
-You drive an hour and 25 each way?

01:00:19.169 --> 01:00:20.052
-Uh, yeah.

01:00:20.119 --> 01:00:22.153
-These gas prices killing you?
-Yes.

01:00:22.473 --> 01:00:23.965
TJ, love the fire.

01:00:24.513 --> 01:00:25.785
-Thank you.
-Best of luck.

01:00:25.852 --> 01:00:27.399
I'm getting ready to leave though.

01:00:27.466 --> 01:00:28.535
-Town?
-Yes.

01:00:28.602 --> 01:00:30.703
-You gonna sell your Airbnbs?
-No.

01:00:31.506 --> 01:00:32.480
I'mma keep them.

01:00:32.547 --> 01:00:35.429
I might come back
when I get about 30 years older.

01:00:45.989 --> 01:00:49.270
Ma'am, TJ told me this side of Main Street,

01:00:49.337 --> 01:00:52.594
everyone's Black,
that side, everyone's White.

01:00:52.661 --> 01:00:54.690
-But you're on the Black side.
-Yeah.

01:00:54.757 --> 01:00:57.109
-How is it?
-It's great to me!

01:00:58.090 --> 01:01:01.573
It don't bother me at all.
It don't bother them. They all my friends.

01:01:01.640 --> 01:01:02.839
-That's cool.

01:01:02.906 --> 01:01:05.443
And you got your friend off camera.
I understand.

01:01:05.510 --> 01:01:07.634
-No. She don't want to be on there.
-Okay.

01:01:07.701 --> 01:01:10.275
So, not a problem at all for you?

01:01:10.342 --> 01:01:11.225
Nope.

01:01:11.642 --> 01:01:12.565
-That's cool.

01:01:12.632 --> 01:01:13.742
We get along good.

01:01:13.809 --> 01:01:16.681
She's my best friend.
That's my granddaughter right there.

01:01:16.748 --> 01:01:19.101
-Oh, nice.
-My great-granddaughter. Yeah.

01:01:19.526 --> 01:01:20.856
We all cool here.

01:01:21.982 --> 01:01:23.709
-[chuckles]
-Did you grow up here?

01:01:23.776 --> 01:01:25.129
I grew up at Snow Lake.

01:01:25.506 --> 01:01:27.023
That's way down the road.

01:01:27.090 --> 01:01:28.266
-Do you like Elaine?

01:01:28.669 --> 01:01:29.728
Yeah. Pretty good.

01:01:30.222 --> 01:01:31.617
And these are TJ's places?

01:01:31.684 --> 01:01:34.003
Yeah. That's TJ's place right there.

01:01:34.412 --> 01:01:36.308
-Take care, ma'am.
-You too.

01:01:36.375 --> 01:01:37.416
All the best.

01:01:37.484 --> 01:01:38.887
-Yeah. Thank you.

01:01:41.115 --> 01:01:42.195
-Yeah, guys.

01:01:42.262 --> 01:01:44.765
It's always a process of discovery.

01:01:46.043 --> 01:01:49.018
And that's what keeps me
doing this work because,

01:01:49.612 --> 01:01:53.189
look, I go into these towns,
I have no idea what I'm coming into.

01:01:53.256 --> 01:01:56.989
For example, Elaine, what TJ said.

01:01:57.615 --> 01:02:00.083
Here are her tiny homes.

01:02:00.546 --> 01:02:02.127
She's renting three of them.

01:02:02.529 --> 01:02:04.235
She's gonna do more she said.

01:02:04.776 --> 01:02:05.894
But that's so cool.

01:02:07.076 --> 01:02:08.841
Super simple. Straightforward.

01:02:09.330 --> 01:02:12.498
That looks like
a brand new one right there.

01:02:16.422 --> 01:02:19.343
So here it is,
Main Street, the dividing line

01:02:20.196 --> 01:02:21.156
in Elaine.

01:02:21.743 --> 01:02:23.037
With a few exceptions.

01:02:24.536 --> 01:02:27.382
Look, I don't have
all the information on this story.

01:02:27.449 --> 01:02:30.273
We'll see if we can
talk to someone on this side.

01:02:39.326 --> 01:02:41.494
Oh, that poor dog's got a hurt leg.

01:02:48.349 --> 01:02:49.584
What a beautiful dog.

01:02:51.137 --> 01:02:52.423
That bums me out.

01:03:03.562 --> 01:03:06.734
Okay, guys, so I'm glad I talked to you.

01:03:06.801 --> 01:03:08.633
You guys don't want to be on camera,

01:03:08.700 --> 01:03:11.075
but you're saying
that's not the case over here.

01:03:11.142 --> 01:03:13.749
Your neighbor's Black over here,
your neighbor's Black over here?

01:03:13.816 --> 01:03:15.861
-Everybody lives…
-It's cool.

01:03:15.928 --> 01:03:17.618
…next ext door to each other.

01:03:17.685 --> 01:03:20.370
There's so many interracial couples here.

01:03:21.649 --> 01:03:23.355
It's not like it used to be.

01:03:23.422 --> 01:03:25.074
-Okay.
-Not at all.

01:03:25.141 --> 01:03:26.207
It's modern.

01:03:26.860 --> 01:03:28.679
More modern now than it was.

01:03:28.746 --> 01:03:30.554
And I love Black women, so… [laughs]

01:03:30.621 --> 01:03:31.809
You do?

01:03:31.876 --> 01:03:34.964
-Now I'm out of here.
-[laughter and car starting]

01:03:35.031 --> 01:03:35.948
[engine revs]

01:03:37.697 --> 01:03:39.873
I kept you off camera, bro. Thank you.

01:03:39.940 --> 01:03:43.336
[car speeds away]

01:03:45.723 --> 01:03:46.606
That was funny.

01:03:47.891 --> 01:03:49.259
So there you go, guys.

01:03:49.326 --> 01:03:52.502
I'm not gonna get to
the total bottom of the story but…

01:03:54.332 --> 01:03:58.786
those guys were cool and they're like,
"I got Black friends and neighbors."

01:03:58.853 --> 01:04:02.974
So I guess it really depends
who you talk to here

01:04:03.801 --> 01:04:04.951
of what's going on.

01:04:05.018 --> 01:04:07.114
I'm not gonna fully understand this town

01:04:07.676 --> 01:04:08.559
in an hour.

01:04:09.109 --> 01:04:12.365
But, hey, we got a little preview
of what it looks like.

01:04:12.432 --> 01:04:16.048
And it is small town, country Delta living.

01:04:21.462 --> 01:04:23.523
All right, guys. What an adventure today.

01:04:23.590 --> 01:04:26.005
We went deep Arkansas Delta.

01:04:26.072 --> 01:04:29.397
Didn't see it all, but definitely got
a good experience today.

01:04:29.464 --> 01:04:31.090
Learned a lot from the locals.

01:04:31.157 --> 01:04:32.344
Saw a lot.

01:04:32.783 --> 01:04:36.576
And unfortunately,
this is the end of the Arkansas series.

01:04:36.999 --> 01:04:38.234
Five videos in total.

01:04:38.637 --> 01:04:40.477
And it's been quite a journey.

01:04:40.544 --> 01:04:42.834
I've loved it.
I've really loved this state.

01:04:42.901 --> 01:04:44.187
It's been a surprise.

01:04:44.602 --> 01:04:47.388
It's full of amazing people.

01:04:47.676 --> 01:04:48.685
Hospitality.

01:04:49.119 --> 01:04:51.413
There are challenges like we saw today.

01:04:51.979 --> 01:04:54.808
And there are places like
Northwestern Arkansas,

01:04:55.190 --> 01:04:57.759
like a different universe economically.

01:04:57.826 --> 01:04:59.331
And a lot in between.

01:04:59.398 --> 01:05:01.002
So check out those other videos.

01:05:01.069 --> 01:05:02.705
I want to thank you,

01:05:02.772 --> 01:05:04.960
all the locals here in the state

01:05:05.027 --> 01:05:08.439
that brought me in,
told me your stories, showed me around.

01:05:09.210 --> 01:05:11.596
And also you, the audience, for watching.

01:05:12.210 --> 01:05:14.290
Thanks for coming along on this journey.

01:05:14.356 --> 01:05:15.474
Until the next one.

01:05:15.541 --> 01:05:17.156
[country music]

